org.hl7.vmr.r2

Class ProcedureBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ClinicalStatement
      • org.hl7.vmr.r2.ProcedureBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProcedureEvent, ProcedureOrder, ProcedureProposal, ScheduledProcedure, UndeliveredProcedure

    public abstract class ProcedureBase
extends ClinicalStatement
    Abstract base class for a procedure, which is a series of steps taken on a subject to accomplish a clinical goal. Procedures include diagnostic testing, consultations, referrals, nursing procedures, making observations, and other clinical interventions excluding substance administrations.

    Java class for ProcedureBase complex type.

     <complexType name="ProcedureBase">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}ClinicalStatement">

         <element name="approachBodySite" type="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}BodySite" minOccurs="0"/>
         <element name="targetBodySite" type="{urn:hl7-org:vmr:r2}BodySite" maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0"/>
       </sequence>
     </extension>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>

      • getTargetBodySite

        public List<BodySite> getTargetBodySite()
        Gets the value of the targetBodySite property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the targetBodySite property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getTargetBodySite().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list BodySite
